# Laravel Quality Analysis with laravel-analyzer

When reviewing or analyzing Laravel PHP files, use the laravel-analyzer MCP tools.

## Available MCP Tools

Use these tools via the MCP server (`laravel-analyzer`):

| Tool | When to use |
|------|------------|
| `analyze` | Full project quality scan |
| `analyze_module` | Focus on one dimension (coupling, testing, debt, complexity, security, owasp) |
| `get_issues` | Get filtered issues by severity |
| `get_recommendations` | Get prioritized action items |

## Quality Thresholds

| Score | Verdict |
|-------|---------|
| ≥ 80 | Good — continue |
| 60–79 | Acceptable — plan improvements |
| 40–59 | Concerning — prioritize this sprint |
| < 40 | Blocking — fix before merging |

## Common Laravel Quality Issues

### Coupling & Cohesion
- God Classes: > 20 methods or > 500 lines → extract into focused services
- High coupling: > 10 injected dependencies → apply Interface Segregation
- Long methods: > 50 lines → extract smaller, named methods

### Security
- `DB::select("... $var")` → use query bindings
- `$guarded = []` or `::create($request->all())` → use `$fillable`
- `{!! $var !!}` → use `{{ $var }}` for user-generated content
- `md5()` / `sha1()` for passwords → use `Hash::make()`

### Complexity
- Cyclomatic complexity > 10 → extract logic, use early returns
- Nesting > 4 levels → use guard clauses and extracted methods
